Is everything okay?

250
00:13:25,763 --> 00:13:26,805
Not really.

251
00:13:26,889 --> 00:13:30,600
When I rented this apartment online,
it never said they don't allow dogs.

252
00:13:30,684 --> 00:13:34,020
And now they won't let us live here.
Yeah, well, it's their loss!

253
00:13:34,855 --> 00:13:39,150
- Do you have someplace else to go?
- Okay, it's my loss and their loss!

254
00:13:39,235 --> 00:13:41,903
(SIGHING) Actually, the only place
I have to go is home.

255
00:13:41,987 --> 00:13:43,655
And trust me, that is not an option!

256
00:13:45,032 --> 00:13:47,575
Listen, there's an empty studio
in my building, if you're interested.

257
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:50,203
I'm friends with the building manager.
I'm sure I can make a call.

258
00:13:51,288 --> 00:13:52,413
And...

259
00:13:53,123 --> 00:13:54,833
Well, I'm sure I can make a call
and arrange something.

260
00:13:54,917 --> 00:13:56,376
Maybe get you to see it.

261
00:13:57,211 --> 00:13:58,169
(SIGHS)

262
00:13:58,254 --> 00:14:02,048
Well, since I don't seem to have
any other options.

263
00:14:04,218 --> 00:14:05,552
Bellman!

264
00:14:12,434 --> 00:14:14,227
Oh, yeah, right. (LAUGHS)

265
00:14:19,066 --> 00:14:20,108
Seriously?

266
00:14:28,576 --> 00:14:31,536
Careful with those!
This is all I have to get by on

267
00:14:31,620 --> 00:14:33,830
until the truck arrives
with the bulk of my things.

268
00:14:45,759 --> 00:14:47,594
(SCREAMING)

269
00:14:47,928 --> 00:14:48,970
Oh! That's good.

270
00:14:49,054 --> 00:14:51,347
Okay, now, go outside,
and then come back in

271
00:14:51,432 --> 00:14:54,684
and give me even more of that
it's-the-end-of-the-world look. Okay?

272
00:14:58,105 --> 00:15:00,023
GIRL 1: Hey, Peyton.
GIRL 2: Hey, Peyton!

273
00:15:00,107 --> 00:15:01,941
- What's up?
- Off to acting class.

274
00:15:02,026 --> 00:15:04,402
(IN SOUTHERN ACCENT)
"Maggie, the cat is alive. I'm alive!"

275
00:15:05,279 --> 00:15:06,654
Singing lesson.

276
00:15:06,739 --> 00:15:09,490
(VOCALIZING IN HIGH VOICE)

277
00:15:09,950 --> 00:15:13,369
Cool, guys. Okay.
Hey, this is Sharpay and Boi.

278
00:15:13,454 --> 00:15:16,331
Hi, Sharpay. Hi, Boi!

279
00:15:16,415 --> 00:15:17,916
Anyways, gotta go. See ya, Peyton.

280
00:15:18,292 --> 00:15:20,501
GIRL 2: Nice meeting you, Sharpay.
PEYTON: Later, guys.

281
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:25,131
Okay. Really, you're going to love
this place. Okay? Up you go.

282
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:32,347
Sorry. It's a pre-war building.

283
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:35,725
And during the war,
they didn't fight for an elevator?

284
00:15:35,809 --> 00:15:38,227
Listen, the building has two things
going for it.

285
00:15:38,312 --> 00:15:41,314
It's got something available,
and I live here.

286
00:15:42,149 --> 00:15:43,650
(SCOFFS)

287
00:15:47,321 --> 00:15:52,325
(SIGHING) Fine. But if I break a heel,
or a sweat, you're responsible.

288
00:15:52,409 --> 00:15:53,868
Get my bags.

289
00:15:58,999 --> 00:16:00,708
(PANTING)

290
00:16:03,837 --> 00:16:05,755
See? That wasn't so bad.

291
00:16:05,839 --> 00:16:08,716
Yeah. Down the hall.

292
00:16:08,801 --> 00:16:11,260
The one with the police tape
and chalk outline.

293
00:16:11,345 --> 00:16:12,804
Really?

294
00:16:12,888 --> 00:16:14,180
Kidding.

295
00:16:31,907 --> 00:16:34,117
- You said this was a studio.
- It is.

296
00:16:34,201 --> 00:16:38,037
No way! MGM was a studio! This?

297
00:16:38,539 --> 00:16:40,456
This is a roach motel
with no room service.

298
00:16:40,541 --> 00:16:41,666
Yeah, a studio apartment.

299
00:16:41,750 --> 00:16:44,210
Sure, from certain angles,
it's a bit small.

300
00:16:44,294 --> 00:16:46,379
A two-karat engagement ring
is a bit small!

301
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:48,756
This is a doll house!

302
00:16:48,841 --> 00:16:51,134
- So what do you think?
- Forget it!

303
00:16:51,218 --> 00:16:54,137
I'd need an entirely separate apartment
just for my lipsticks.

304
00:16:54,221 --> 00:16:56,180
And where am I supposed to sleep?

305
00:17:05,315 --> 00:17:07,400
- What is that?
- It's your bed.

306
00:17:07,484 --> 00:17:10,403
That is not a bed.
It's a closet with a tongue.

307
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:12,071
You can't be serious!

308
00:17:12,156 --> 00:17:15,658
- There is one really good thing about it.
- Yeah, sure.

309
00:17:22,249 --> 00:17:25,877
See? This is my place!
Looking better, huh?

310
00:17:26,378 --> 00:17:29,172
Am I missing something? Oh, right.

311
00:17:29,256 --> 00:17:31,883
Space! Luxury! Maid service!

312
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:34,260
Let me guess.
You're used to being spoiled.

313
00:17:34,386 --> 00:17:37,180
I'm not used to it. I just expect it.

314
00:17:37,264 --> 00:17:39,640
You know, half this building
is filled with performers

315
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:42,351
who came here
with the same ambitions you did.

316
00:17:42,436 --> 00:17:43,978
What makes you
so much better than them?

317
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:48,483
Money, breeding, talent, great hair,
perfect jaw line, chic taste.

318
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:49,901
How much time do you have?

319
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:52,111
All right, fine.

320
00:17:52,196 --> 00:17:53,780
I tried to help you out
like my mom asked,

321
00:17:53,864 --> 00:17:55,531
but whatever.
I'll find someone else to film.

322
00:17:57,159 --> 00:17:59,202
The only problem is if I call my father

323
00:17:59,286 --> 00:18:01,579
and tell him how I messed up
on the other apartment

324
00:18:01,663 --> 00:18:05,208
and how I have nowhere to go but here,
and I ask for his help,

325
00:18:05,292 --> 00:18:06,793
he'll make me come home and...

326
00:18:06,877 --> 00:18:08,294
(STAMMERING)

327
00:18:08,629 --> 00:18:09,629
Work!

328
00:18:09,838 --> 00:18:12,507
- So?
- So? Then I'll never get my big break.

329
00:18:12,966 --> 00:18:15,176
Oh, and promise you won't call
your mother and tell her about this,

330
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:17,345
because then she'll call my mom
who will tell my dad,

331
00:18:17,429 --> 00:18:19,764
and I don't think he really believes
I can make this happen.

332
00:18:19,848 --> 00:18:21,182
He only gave me one month to prove it.

333
00:18:21,266 --> 00:18:23,392
Well, then you've got one month
to prove him wrong.

334
00:18:23,477 --> 00:18:24,852
(GROANS)

335
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:26,854
Why did I do this?

336
00:18:27,022 --> 00:18:30,316
I want my canopy bed
and my housekeeper.

337
00:18:30,484 --> 00:18:32,652
And a shower that doesn't share a room
with a kitchen.

338
00:18:36,281 --> 00:18:37,406
- Come on.
- Where to?

339
00:18:37,491 --> 00:18:40,201
- Do you trust me?
- You suggested this place.

340
00:18:40,285 --> 00:18:41,285
Yeah. Point taken. Come anyway.
Come on.

341
00:18:45,457 --> 00:18:47,250
SHARPAY: I hope you're taking me
to a better apartment

342
00:18:47,334 --> 00:18:48,376
than what you just showed me.

343
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:52,255
Because let me tell you, if that's it?
No way! Absolutely no!

344
00:18:52,339 --> 00:18:54,674
Just come on.
Just don't ask any questions.

345
00:18:54,758 --> 00:18:57,385
I need luxury! Are you kidding me?

346
00:18:57,469 --> 00:19:01,180
That was like a green, dark hole
that I never wanna be in ever again.

347
00:19:01,265 --> 00:19:02,849
All right, here you go.

348
00:19:03,684 --> 00:19:04,684
Butchy!

349
00:19:07,187 --> 00:19:08,479
- Come on...
- Where are you taking me?

350
00:19:08,564 --> 00:19:11,107
- You'll see. Come on.
- Why are we here?

351
00:19:11,191 --> 00:19:13,276
All right, all right. Now, you're gonna
have to close your eyes.

352
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:14,944
- Close my eyes?
- Yeah, just close your eyes.

353
00:19:15,028 --> 00:19:17,238
- Why?
- Because! Just do it.

354
00:19:17,322 --> 00:19:19,282
All right, now. Keep them closed.

355
00:19:19,366 --> 00:19:22,827
- Well, what if I hit into something?
- You won't. I got you.

356
00:19:22,911 --> 00:19:27,081
All right, all right. Keep them closed.
All right.

357
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:28,833
- All right, you got them closed?
- Yes, I do.

358
00:19:28,917 --> 00:19:31,711
All right, all right. Perfect. All right.
Now, stay here, keep them closed.

359
00:19:31,795 --> 00:19:32,837
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

360
00:19:32,921 --> 00:19:37,216
Keep them closed. All righty.
Keep them closed.

361
00:19:38,719 --> 00:19:41,179
All right. Open them. Hit it, Butchy!

362
00:19:50,397 --> 00:19:51,564
Wow.

363
00:19:59,573 --> 00:20:01,407
I know.

364
00:20:01,491 --> 00:20:06,329
When I left Indiana to go to school here,
I didn't know a soul either,

365
00:20:06,413 --> 00:20:08,998
and I was just as overwhelmed as you.

366
00:20:09,082 --> 00:20:12,084
But I had two things,
my dream and my camera.

367
00:20:13,086 --> 00:20:14,754
And look at me now.

368
00:20:15,881 --> 00:20:18,507
You still only have your dream
and your camera.

369
00:20:18,592 --> 00:20:22,428
Yes, but I met you, didn't I?
So, something's working out.

370
00:20:23,347 --> 00:20:25,514
Well, whenever people meet me,
things get better.

371
00:20:25,599 --> 00:20:26,849
(LAUGHS)

372
00:20:27,976 --> 00:20:31,270
Look, you just have to adapt
to your surroundings.

373
00:20:31,396 --> 00:20:34,899
And remember that for now
this is all just temporary.

374
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:39,987
Right. Like prom dresses
and first boyfriends.

375
00:20:42,449 --> 00:20:46,494
Look, anything you have to do
will be worth it to get your dream.

376
00:20:49,122 --> 00:20:50,248
Okay.

377
00:20:50,999 --> 00:20:53,376
I'm gonna meet with
that casting director, get the part,

378
00:20:53,460 --> 00:20:56,420
- be a star and have a palace!
- There you go.

379
00:20:56,505 --> 00:20:59,674
That's the self-indulgent, self-entitled,
optimistic pink hurricane

380
00:20:59,758 --> 00:21:00,841
I've been seeing through my lens.

381
00:21:01,510 --> 00:21:04,095
And I like how perceptive you are.

382
00:21:04,930 --> 00:21:06,973
Okay, New York. Bring it on.

383
00:21:13,355 --> 00:21:15,439
(UPBEAT POP SONG PLAYING)

384
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:20,236
(SINGING)
I used to think maybe you loved me

385
00:21:20,320 --> 00:21:23,155
Now, baby, I'm sure

386
00:21:25,784 --> 00:21:31,122
And I just can't wait till the day
When you knock on my door

387
00:21:31,206 --> 00:21:32,581
(SQUEALING)

388
00:21:34,334 --> 00:21:40,673
Now every time I go for the mailbox
Gotta hold myself down

389
00:21:43,093 --> 00:21:49,015
"Cause I just can't wait till you write me
You're coming around

390
00:21:50,809 --> 00:21:53,686
I'm walking on sunshine

391
00:21:54,813 --> 00:21:55,896
(BARKS)

392
00:21:55,981 --> 00:21:58,232
I'm walking on sunshine

393
00:21:59,776 --> 00:22:02,194
I'm walking on sunshine, whoa

394
00:22:02,946 --> 00:22:04,155
(WHOOPS)

395
00:22:04,239 --> 00:22:07,116
- And don't it feel good!
- Hey!

396
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:10,453
All right now
And don't it feel good!

397
00:22:10,537 --> 00:22:11,579
Hey!

398
00:22:11,663 --> 00:22:14,790
All right now, yeah

399
00:22:14,875 --> 00:22:16,000
Hi!

400
00:22:19,046 --> 00:22:20,421
(SHRIEKING)

401
00:22:22,632 --> 00:22:24,550
Turn it off. Turn it off!

402
00:22:26,219 --> 00:22:28,512
(SINGING) Just waiting foryou

403
00:22:29,556 --> 00:22:31,557
CHORUS: Just waiting for you

404
00:22:31,641 --> 00:22:34,894
Now I don't want you back
for the weekend

405
00:22:34,978 --> 00:22:37,313
Not back for a day

406
00:22:37,397 --> 00:22:39,148
No, no, no

407
00:22:39,232 --> 00:22:40,399
(LAUGHING)

408
00:22:42,235 --> 00:22:43,277
What?

409
00:22:43,737 --> 00:22:46,280
I want you to stay

410
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:59,627
I'm walking on sunshine

411
00:23:01,421 --> 00:23:04,465
- And don't it feel good!
- CHORUS: Hey!

412
00:23:04,549 --> 00:23:07,927
All right now
And don't it feel good!

413
00:23:08,011 --> 00:23:09,428
SHARPAY: Oh, yeah!

414
00:23:10,263 --> 00:23:13,599
PEYTON: Looking good. So pink.

415
00:23:16,436 --> 00:23:17,812
You're good.

416
00:23:20,774 --> 00:23:22,817
(BOTH CHATTERING)

417
00:23:23,777 --> 00:23:26,404
- Do you wanna try some?
- No, I don't want any!

418
00:23:26,488 --> 00:23:27,488
(BOTH LAUGHING)

419
00:23:28,573 --> 00:23:31,117
Lay down. Lay down.

420
00:23:33,370 --> 00:23:35,246
(LAUGHS) Night, Boi!

421
00:23:44,798 --> 00:23:46,173
(SHARPAY SQUEALING)

422
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:51,887
(MUFFLED) Boi? Get help!

423
00:23:51,972 --> 00:23:52,972
(BANGING ON DOOR)

424
00:23:54,641 --> 00:23:55,933
(FAKING GASP)

425
00:23:57,394 --> 00:23:58,978
- PEYTON: Knock, knock.
- Come in!

426
00:24:02,315 --> 00:24:05,901
Wow! And wow.

427
00:24:09,030 --> 00:24:11,115
Hey, are you on your way to meet
with the casting director?

428
00:24:11,199 --> 00:24:14,869
No, I'm on my way
to change theater history.

429
00:24:14,953 --> 00:24:16,787
You think this is a good outfit
for changing history?

430
00:24:20,292 --> 00:24:22,877
Perfect! Mind if I tag along and film?

431
00:24:22,961 --> 00:24:25,171
Not that you could ever mind me, right?

432
00:24:25,255 --> 00:24:27,423
I think you should. After all,

433
00:24:28,175 --> 00:24:31,469
not many people can say they were
there to film the creation of a legend.

434
00:24:39,019 --> 00:24:40,811
Sharpay! You made it after all!

435
00:24:40,896 --> 00:24:43,481
Destiny called,
and I get great reception!

436
00:24:43,565 --> 00:24:46,775
Well, your timing is perfect.
What's tomorrow like for you?

437
00:24:46,860 --> 00:24:49,361
The first day of the rest of my fame.

438
00:24:49,446 --> 00:24:51,614
Well, all right.
I'll set up your audition for 3:00.

439
00:24:51,698 --> 00:24:54,158
I'll e-mail you the musical number
that we'd like you to prepare.

440
00:24:54,242 --> 00:24:56,785
And could you make sure
that he's well-groomed

441
00:24:56,870 --> 00:25:00,414
and, you know,
takes care of any business beforehand.

442
00:25:00,499 --> 00:25:02,541
- What?
- What?

443
00:25:02,626 --> 00:25:03,626
- He?
- Yes.

444
00:25:03,710 --> 00:25:04,668
- Him?
- Him.

445
00:25:04,753 --> 00:25:05,753
- He?
- Yes!

446
00:25:05,837 --> 00:25:06,837
Wait, what?

447
00:25:08,048 --> 00:25:11,217
It's your dog that we want to audition.
He was amazing!

448
00:25:11,885 --> 00:25:13,010
Oh.

449
00:25:13,094 --> 00:25:14,094
(LOUDLY) What?

450
00:25:15,305 --> 00:25:16,305
I mean...

451
00:25:17,057 --> 00:25:19,767
I sent you all the information
in response to your e-mail.

452
00:25:19,893 --> 00:25:23,145
I mean, didn't the title of the musical
give you any indication?

453
00:25:23,271 --> 00:25:24,522
A Girl's Best Friend?

454
00:25:24,606 --> 00:25:26,899
A Girl's Best Friend!
And I'm here for the girl!

455
00:25:27,359 --> 00:25:28,359
You're here for the girl?

456
00:25:28,443 --> 00:25:29,860
Well, I'm never the best friend!

457
00:25:30,612 --> 00:25:32,488
Oh, no. No, no. We wanted Boi.

458
00:25:32,989 --> 00:25:33,989
As the girl?

459
00:25:34,074 --> 00:25:35,157
No, as the best friend.

460
00:25:35,242 --> 00:25:37,660
Wait, wait. You wanted Boi
as the best friend of the girl?

461
00:25:37,744 --> 00:25:39,078
Not me as the girl with the best friend?

462
00:25:39,162 --> 00:25:40,162
Exactly.

463
00:25:41,540 --> 00:25:44,291
Oh, Sharpay, I am so sorry
for the confusion.

464
00:25:44,918 --> 00:25:47,670
If you don't want Boi to audition,
I would totally understand.

465
00:25:50,966 --> 00:25:55,135
Sharpay. Sharpay! Hey, stop.

466
00:25:55,220 --> 00:25:56,845
MAN: Hey, don't touch the car!

467
00:25:57,097 --> 00:25:59,807
Look, slow down. Even New Yorkers
can't keep up with you.

468
00:25:59,891 --> 00:26:01,517
It's not even me they wanted!

469
00:26:01,601 --> 00:26:03,686
Well, to be fair, the role is for a dog.

470
00:26:03,770 --> 00:26:05,729
If they wanted you,
I could understand you being upset.

471
00:26:05,897 --> 00:26:07,398
Why did I come all this way?

472
00:26:07,482 --> 00:26:10,401
Leave my friends, family,
a dry, self-hydrating climate?

473
00:26:10,527 --> 00:26:13,696
To follow your dream!
Or at least that's what I thought.

474
00:26:14,281 --> 00:26:16,615
Nothing is turning out
the way I planned it!

475
00:26:16,700 --> 00:26:18,993
Plan A. Live in a penthouse
and star on Broadway.

476
00:26:19,119 --> 00:26:20,953
Plan B... Don't have a plan B!

477
00:26:21,121 --> 00:26:22,538
What do I tell my father now?

478
00:26:22,622 --> 00:26:25,499
That you came to a very special city
determined to be someone very special,

479
00:26:25,584 --> 00:26:26,584
which you are.

480
00:26:27,043 --> 00:26:29,920
Oh, I'm not so special.
I'm just like everyone else.

481
00:26:30,005 --> 00:26:31,171
Maybe a little better.

482
00:26:31,256 --> 00:26:32,214
Look at it this way.

483
00:26:32,299 --> 00:26:36,176
Boi is your dog, and he has
an opportunity, so be happy for him.

484
00:26:38,763 --> 00:26:39,763
You're right.

485
00:26:40,599 --> 00:26:44,476
I'm being, you know, what's the word?
When you do something for yourself

486
00:26:44,561 --> 00:26:46,228
even though it's
not so good for other people?

487
00:26:46,396 --> 00:26:48,022
- Selfish?
- No!

488
00:26:48,982 --> 00:26:49,982
Oh, yeah.

489
00:26:51,067 --> 00:26:54,612
Look, Sharpay,
you can't give up. Okay?

490
00:26:55,071 --> 00:26:58,240
And, anyway,
you're officially the star of my film.

491
00:26:58,617 --> 00:26:59,575
I am?

492
00:26:59,659 --> 00:27:00,909
Yeah, you are.

493
00:27:00,994 --> 00:27:03,704
Oh. So now it's all about you?

