00:41:53,719 --> 00:41:55,512
(LAUGHING)

746
00:41:56,263 --> 00:41:58,806
- Why is that funny?
- Well...

747
00:41:58,891 --> 00:42:00,308
Because you'd rather have the...

748
00:42:02,228 --> 00:42:04,729
I'll explain later. Just keep going.

749
00:42:06,398 --> 00:42:09,275
There's only one thing
that breaks my heart.

750
00:42:09,360 --> 00:42:11,528
Leaving Shelby behind.

751
00:42:11,904 --> 00:42:16,074
Pick it up! Go, go!
A star is about to be born!

752
00:42:17,910 --> 00:42:18,952
Shelby!

753
00:42:19,036 --> 00:42:20,161
Oh!

754
00:42:20,246 --> 00:42:23,498
What's in this envelope?
This very wet envelope.

755
00:42:23,582 --> 00:42:25,500
(LAUGHING)

756
00:42:25,584 --> 00:42:28,503
- Again, I don't get that.
- Keep going.

757
00:42:29,755 --> 00:42:31,047
Gasp!

758
00:42:31,131 --> 00:42:34,467
Actually, that's a stage direction.

759
00:42:34,552 --> 00:42:36,010
You gasp, you don't say "gasp."

760
00:42:36,095 --> 00:42:38,263
GILL: Simple mistake. Keep going.

761
00:42:38,764 --> 00:42:40,181
(GASPS)

762
00:42:40,266 --> 00:42:42,684
Shelby! Trying to run away
with my boarding pass

763
00:42:42,768 --> 00:42:45,979
won't change the fact
that I'm leaving at 8:00 a.m.

764
00:42:46,939 --> 00:42:48,106
6:00 a.m.

765
00:42:48,732 --> 00:42:50,316
(LAUGHS)

766
00:42:52,570 --> 00:42:53,945
(BARKS)

767
00:42:54,029 --> 00:42:57,282
Oh, Shelby.
This is the first time we'll be apart.

768
00:42:57,366 --> 00:43:00,159
I wish I could just pack you up
in a widdle doggie bag.

769
00:43:00,244 --> 00:43:01,369
(CHUCKLING)

770
00:43:01,453 --> 00:43:05,707
Okay. Let's get Countess in there
and continue.

771
00:43:05,791 --> 00:43:07,292
Don't worry, sweetheart.

772
00:43:07,376 --> 00:43:09,919
Shelby and I will both be here
when you get back.

773
00:43:15,676 --> 00:43:16,843
You're killing me.

774
00:43:19,263 --> 00:43:20,597
AMBER LEE: Oh!

775
00:43:20,681 --> 00:43:22,432
NEAL: That is adorable!

776
00:43:22,808 --> 00:43:25,852
AMBER LEE: You're right, Shelby!
Why not go with me?

777
00:43:25,936 --> 00:43:28,938
Any place that doesn't want you,
I don't wanna be.

778
00:43:31,525 --> 00:43:33,026
Let's see what New York
has in store for us together!

779
00:43:35,195 --> 00:43:36,279
Good.

780
00:43:36,780 --> 00:43:40,366
Let's talk about the scene a bit,
and we'll do it again.

781
00:43:40,451 --> 00:43:42,577
And both dogs, great work!

782
00:44:12,608 --> 00:44:15,652
Shelby! Trying to run away
with my boarding pass

783
00:44:15,736 --> 00:44:18,946
won't change the fact
that I'm leaving at 8:00 a.m.

784
00:44:19,990 --> 00:44:21,407
6:00 a.m.

785
00:44:28,082 --> 00:44:31,209
What's going on? The dog.
What is this?

786
00:44:31,502 --> 00:44:34,295
Somebody, please.
The dog is licking me.

787
00:44:34,380 --> 00:44:36,673
All right, all right. Get me the other dog!

788
00:44:36,757 --> 00:44:37,965
(SIGHING)

789
00:44:38,050 --> 00:44:40,301
Sorry. What can you do?

790
00:44:46,934 --> 00:44:49,894
There's only one thing
that breaks my heart.

791
00:44:50,729 --> 00:44:52,689
Leaving Shelby behind.

792
00:44:52,773 --> 00:44:53,856
Okay, go, go!

793
00:44:57,403 --> 00:44:58,486
(DOG WHISTLE BLOWING)

794
00:45:07,246 --> 00:45:10,039
- GILL: Why is she twirling?
- What is she doing?

795
00:45:10,124 --> 00:45:11,499
(GROANING)

796
00:45:11,583 --> 00:45:13,334
- Gill?
- Roger!

797
00:45:13,460 --> 00:45:15,670
Figure out what's going on with the dog.
It's not helping me.

798
00:45:15,754 --> 00:45:18,297
- Not helping, people!
- Meanwhile, get the other dog!

799
00:45:20,718 --> 00:45:23,469
Sorry. What can you do?

800
00:45:26,557 --> 00:45:28,850
AMBER LEE: There's only one thing
that breaks my heart.

801
00:45:28,934 --> 00:45:30,852
Leaving Shelby behind.

802
00:45:30,936 --> 00:45:32,103
Okay, go!

803
00:45:33,772 --> 00:45:35,440
Oh, hey!

804
00:45:38,110 --> 00:45:39,068
(BARKS)

805
00:45:39,153 --> 00:45:40,236
(CAT MEWING)

806
00:45:42,364 --> 00:45:43,573
(CAT SCREECHING)

807
00:45:43,657 --> 00:45:44,949
(CRASHING)

808
00:45:45,951 --> 00:45:47,243
(EXCLAIMING)

809
00:45:48,287 --> 00:45:50,496
How is this helping? Really.

810
00:45:50,581 --> 00:45:53,249
Am I the only one bothered by this?
Gill?

811
00:45:53,584 --> 00:45:55,376
Okay, everybody, that's 10!

812
00:46:01,049 --> 00:46:04,302
I'll admit you're good. But we're better.
Give up!

813
00:46:04,386 --> 00:46:05,470
Give up?

814
00:46:05,554 --> 00:46:08,639
Not until there's a Broadway marquee
with a picture of my dog so big

815
00:46:08,724 --> 00:46:10,224
you can walk by
and smell his puppy breath!

816
00:46:10,309 --> 00:46:13,519
I have to take the dogs for a nap.
Union rules.

817
00:46:14,646 --> 00:46:16,022
Thank you.

818
00:46:20,819 --> 00:46:22,737
- You break first.
- No, you break first.

819
00:46:36,251 --> 00:46:37,919
AMBER LEE: Oh!

820
00:46:39,087 --> 00:46:42,131
- Pretty cute, huh?
- Yeah! Yes, they are!

821
00:46:42,216 --> 00:46:45,802
I just wanted to tell you something.

822
00:46:47,346 --> 00:46:50,473
This is my show.
I'm America's sweetheart.

823
00:46:50,557 --> 00:46:53,518
They're paying to see me,
not you two over-bred fur balls.

824
00:46:54,394 --> 00:46:58,105
So, until I can figure out a way
to get rid of you,

825
00:46:59,566 --> 00:47:01,818
you better watch your step,

826
00:47:01,902 --> 00:47:03,528
otherwise you'll find out
the real meaning

827
00:47:03,612 --> 00:47:06,489
of going home in a doggie bag.
(CHUCKLES EVILLY)

828
00:47:20,546 --> 00:47:23,172
PEYTON: This film
is cutting together really well.

829
00:47:23,257 --> 00:47:24,715
Do I look amazing?

830
00:47:24,800 --> 00:47:27,343
- The camera loves you.
- I know!

831
00:47:27,427 --> 00:47:28,427
(COMPUTER CHIMES)

832
00:47:28,554 --> 00:47:31,389
Oh, no! My dad's video-chatting me.

833
00:47:31,473 --> 00:47:33,307
He thinks I live in a penthouse.

834
00:47:33,392 --> 00:47:36,644
I can't let him see that I live
in a tiny studio in a filthy tenement.

835
00:47:36,728 --> 00:47:37,854
With a boy in my room!

836
00:47:37,938 --> 00:47:40,398
A boy, by the way, that has no money,
and lives in a tinier studio,

837
00:47:40,482 --> 00:47:43,442
and who, apparently, has never heard
of the word "maid-service"! No offense.

838
00:47:43,527 --> 00:47:44,861
What of that could possibly offend me?

839
00:47:44,945 --> 00:47:47,780
(PANTING) Oh, my! Oh, my!
I don't know. Hyperventilating!

840
00:47:47,865 --> 00:47:50,366
- What do I do? What do I do?
- Come on.

841
00:47:51,952 --> 00:47:53,911
- Come on. Hurry!
- (COMPUTER CHIMING)

842
00:47:56,832 --> 00:47:59,166
- All right, scoot over. Okay, go, go.
- Okay, I gotta get this. Stop!

843
00:47:59,251 --> 00:48:00,459
Hi, Daddy!

844
00:48:00,544 --> 00:48:03,337
Hey, princess! How's my little girl?

845
00:48:03,422 --> 00:48:05,756
Overpaying for everything
and yelling at total strangers.

846
00:48:05,841 --> 00:48:07,967
(EXCLAIMS)
You're practically a native.

847
00:48:08,051 --> 00:48:11,137
Hey, where are you?
That view is spectacular.

848
00:48:11,221 --> 00:48:12,680
Well, there's hardly a penthouse
in the city

849
00:48:12,764 --> 00:48:14,599
that doesn't have a spectacular view!

850
00:48:15,100 --> 00:48:17,184
So, you the toast of Broadway?

851
00:48:17,269 --> 00:48:19,770
Daddy, you know how I feel
about carb references.

852
00:48:20,731 --> 00:48:22,565
Just a little concerned, sweetie.

853
00:48:22,649 --> 00:48:24,650
The last time no one's heard from you
for this long

854
00:48:24,776 --> 00:48:27,361
was when you found out your gold card
wasn't actually made of gold.

855
00:48:27,446 --> 00:48:29,739
Well, I've been busy with rehearsals.

856
00:48:29,823 --> 00:48:32,325
Outstanding! You got into the show?

857
00:48:32,409 --> 00:48:35,369
Well, it doesn't quite work like that.
It's complicated.

858
00:48:35,454 --> 00:48:37,121
But I know it's gonna work out.

859
00:48:37,205 --> 00:48:39,957
Sharpay, is there something
you're not telling me?

860
00:48:40,042 --> 00:48:42,209
You remember the deal, right?
If things aren't working out...

861
00:48:42,294 --> 00:48:45,087
I know, I know. I have one month
to get in the show, and then...

862
00:48:45,172 --> 00:48:48,341
Two weeks, sweetie.
You have two weeks left.

863
00:48:49,718 --> 00:48:51,385
You're sure everything's okay?

864
00:48:51,470 --> 00:48:52,845
It's fine, Daddy.

865
00:48:53,138 --> 00:48:57,475
Well, okay. We miss you, angel.

866
00:48:57,893 --> 00:48:58,976
Miss you, too.

867
00:48:59,061 --> 00:49:00,436
I love you!

868
00:49:04,816 --> 00:49:09,487
Boi has to get that role. I can't go home.
Not as a failure.

869
00:49:10,280 --> 00:49:14,241
I need some sort of subtle,
visibly crushing advantage over Roger.

870
00:49:14,326 --> 00:49:16,953
Look, why not just trust Boi is talented,
that you've trained him well,

871
00:49:17,037 --> 00:49:19,664
- and let fate take it from there.
- Fate?

872
00:49:19,748 --> 00:49:22,333
Fate gave a girl in my graduating class
one long eyebrow.

873
00:49:23,085 --> 00:49:24,168
I can't trust fate.

874
00:49:25,963 --> 00:49:27,922
Some matters you just have to
take into your own hands.

875
00:49:28,715 --> 00:49:31,509
What do you mean
you forgot my bottled water?

876
00:49:31,927 --> 00:49:35,096
Well, I was going to get
those magazines

877
00:49:35,180 --> 00:49:36,597
that you said you wanted
from across town,

878
00:49:36,682 --> 00:49:38,766
and I got hit by a bike messenger.

879
00:49:38,850 --> 00:49:41,936
So I went to the hospital for, like,
just one second to get these stitches.

880
00:49:42,020 --> 00:49:44,063
And meanwhile, I had no water!

881
00:49:44,147 --> 00:49:45,439
I will get it for you right now.

882
00:49:45,524 --> 00:49:47,441
Now I've had to drink tap!

883
00:49:47,526 --> 00:49:49,944
- I am so sorry.
- (MOCKING) "I am so sorry."

884
00:49:50,028 --> 00:49:51,946
- I will do better.
- Forget it, okay?

885
00:49:52,030 --> 00:49:53,197
Aside from catching some shade

886
00:49:53,281 --> 00:49:55,658
from the shadow cast
by your madam's apple,

887
00:49:55,742 --> 00:49:59,662
you're of no use to me.
You're... (WHIMPERING) fired!

888
00:50:02,499 --> 00:50:03,874
(CRYING) God!

889
00:50:14,720 --> 00:50:16,095
Amber Lee?

890
00:50:17,305 --> 00:50:20,391
Oh, wow! You look so cute, Sharpie!

891
00:50:20,517 --> 00:50:22,309
- Sharpay.
- You changed it.

892
00:50:22,394 --> 00:50:26,147
I like that even better.
So, tell me, what's on your mind?

893
00:50:26,231 --> 00:50:29,150
I just saw your assistant leave in tears.

894
00:50:29,234 --> 00:50:31,694
She's not my assistant. She quit.

895
00:50:32,738 --> 00:50:34,655
No wonder she was crying.

896
00:50:34,740 --> 00:50:37,283
Yeah, I don't think
she even really cared.

897
00:50:37,367 --> 00:50:40,578
Next time I should probably
just hire a best friend instead.

898
00:50:43,623 --> 00:50:44,623
Wait!

899
00:50:45,542 --> 00:50:46,834
Are you thinking what I'm thinking?

900
00:50:46,918 --> 00:50:48,419
What are you thinking
that I should be thinking?

901
00:50:48,503 --> 00:50:50,504
I could help you out
until you replace her.

902
00:50:50,589 --> 00:50:52,590
That is what I was thinking
about thinking.

903
00:50:52,674 --> 00:50:54,842
Of course this can't, in any way,
affect your decision

904
00:50:54,926 --> 00:50:56,510
of which dog gets the starring role.

905
00:50:56,595 --> 00:50:58,179
Oh, it won't.

906
00:50:58,638 --> 00:51:01,849
I couldn't live with myself
if I thought I did anything unfair.

907
00:51:02,768 --> 00:51:06,145
You have my word. Hey, I know!
How about dinner?

908
00:51:07,272 --> 00:51:09,023
- That sounds awesome!
- Right?

909
00:51:09,107 --> 00:51:12,526
Get me a reservation for two
at someplace fantastic.

910
00:51:12,611 --> 00:51:14,779
Then call my agent, have her meet me.

911
00:51:15,739 --> 00:51:17,698
Right. Sure.

912
00:51:20,243 --> 00:51:24,747
Oh. I won't forget this. And I promise,

913
00:51:24,831 --> 00:51:26,540
it won't be because you're helping me

914
00:51:26,625 --> 00:51:30,127
if I happen to take a little extra liking
to Girl.

915
00:51:31,046 --> 00:51:33,214
- Boi.
- You changed it.

916
00:51:33,298 --> 00:51:35,216
I like that even better.

917
00:51:35,300 --> 00:51:37,259
Oh, and can you take my mic down
to the sound guy

918
00:51:37,344 --> 00:51:40,554
- and tell him the wire hurts my scalp.
- Okay.

919
00:51:40,639 --> 00:51:42,473
You're the best.

920
00:51:45,644 --> 00:51:48,187
Amber Lee says
the wire is hurting her scalp.

921
00:51:48,271 --> 00:51:49,939
Personally,
I think she's using the wrong shampoo,

922
00:51:50,023 --> 00:51:51,899
but she's the star, and you know,
I don't wanna say anything.

923
00:51:51,983 --> 00:51:53,067
You're hot.

924
00:51:54,402 --> 00:51:55,486
Excuse me?

925
00:51:56,238 --> 00:51:57,363
You're hot.

926
00:51:58,490 --> 00:52:01,784
Okay. Even though theater lighting
highlights my natural skin tones,

927
00:52:01,868 --> 00:52:04,411
thank you for noticing,
that's a little rude, don't you think?

928
00:52:04,496 --> 00:52:06,372
No. Your mic's hot.

929
00:52:07,749 --> 00:52:09,083
It means it's on.

930
00:52:09,167 --> 00:52:11,710
You see that little switch.
When it's flipped over like that,

931
00:52:11,795 --> 00:52:15,714
it means it's on
and it's going through the entire theater.

932
00:52:16,258 --> 00:52:19,009
Well, you could have led
with that part, thank you.

933
00:52:19,094 --> 00:52:20,928
Amber Lee's got a great scalp!

934
00:52:26,476 --> 00:52:28,602
(LAUGHS) You're hot.

935
00:52:28,687 --> 00:52:31,522
Then she asked me to help her out
after her assistant quit.

936
00:52:31,606 --> 00:52:33,649
And after I suggested it.

937
00:52:33,733 --> 00:52:35,151
Are you sure this is wise?

938
00:52:35,235 --> 00:52:38,320
I'm sorry. Let me re-phrase that.
This isn't wise.

939
00:52:38,405 --> 00:52:42,199
It's perfect. Amber Lee will see
that she and I are exactly alike,

940
00:52:42,325 --> 00:52:44,869
we'll become BFFs,
she'll make sure Boi gets the role,

941
00:52:44,953 --> 00:52:46,871
then his fame becomes my fame!

942
00:52:46,955 --> 00:52:49,290
I mean, this is the advantage
I've been waiting for!

943
00:52:49,374 --> 00:52:50,708
Isn't it more like taking advantage?

944
00:52:50,792 --> 00:52:52,710
And my father thought
I couldn't do this in a month.

945
00:52:52,794 --> 00:52:55,254
It's turning out better than I imagined.

946
00:52:56,256 --> 00:52:57,965
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

947
00:53:05,557 --> 00:53:06,765
Hello?

948
00:53:08,268 --> 00:53:10,186
Sure. Be right over.

949
00:53:12,689 --> 00:53:14,023
(SIGHING)

950
00:53:18,445 --> 00:53:19,737
Hello?

951
00:53:21,072 --> 00:53:23,032
Oh, thank goodness. In here, quickly.

952
00:53:32,417 --> 00:53:34,668
I just... I can't reach that.

953
00:53:36,504 --> 00:53:38,255
Can't reach it?

954
00:53:39,758 --> 00:53:43,844
Okay, it was a little bit of a test.

955
00:53:45,805 --> 00:53:48,140
Only a true friend would come
all the way down here at this hour

956
00:53:48,225 --> 00:53:49,600
and help me with something like that.

957
00:53:54,439 --> 00:53:56,315
- So, I passed?
- Yes.

958
00:53:56,441 --> 00:53:57,441
(GIGGLING)

959
00:53:57,776 --> 00:53:59,860
- But, seriously, the purse.
- Okay.

960
00:54:12,832 --> 00:54:14,291
Thank you.

961
00:54:19,297 --> 00:54:22,800
All right, here's your bag.
Here's your other bag.

962
00:54:23,635 --> 00:54:24,885
Oh, and don't forget your photo shoot.

963
00:54:24,970 --> 00:54:27,763
Oh, you're a lifesaver.
You must be at that photo shoot

964
00:54:27,847 --> 00:54:30,557
to make sure I look as fabulous
as you always do.

965
00:54:30,642 --> 00:54:34,228
- Are you serious?
- Serious? You're now also my stylist.

966
00:54:34,479 --> 00:54:36,730
You have to tell me all your secrets.
Okay, gotta go.

967
00:54:47,492 --> 00:54:49,201
"Life is so strange.

968
00:54:49,286 --> 00:54:53,414
"Shelby and I travel halfway across
the country to find fame and fortune,

969
00:54:53,498 --> 00:54:56,083
"and instead, we find love."

970
00:54:57,711 --> 00:55:02,673
Hey! How about dinner?
Split some egg rolls at Wok This Way?

971
00:55:03,383 --> 00:55:06,427
Can't. I have to highlight script changes
for Amber Lee,

972
00:55:06,511 --> 00:55:09,972
then highlight her hair.
Highlight of my night!

973
00:55:10,348 --> 00:55:14,018
Okay.
But I miss spending time with you.

974
00:55:14,519 --> 00:55:16,895
And you did promise to shoot
some more stuff for my film.

975
00:55:17,355 --> 00:55:20,399
You know,
what I'm doing is important, too.

976
00:55:20,483 --> 00:55:21,525
Oh.

977
00:55:21,609 --> 00:55:24,653
For a minute there,
you sounded like Amber Lee.

978
00:55:30,410 --> 00:55:35,831
"Good to see you. Good to see
you. Good to see you. Good to see you."

979
00:55:37,542 --> 00:55:41,503
Bad news. My maid quit.
So, here's a list of chores.

980
00:55:42,714 --> 00:55:43,881
Chores?

981
00:55:44,966 --> 00:55:50,596
And I want to talk to you about Boi.

982
00:55:51,389 --> 00:55:53,098
But you have to promise
it'll stay between us.

983
00:55:53,808 --> 00:55:54,975
Okay.

984
00:55:56,102 --> 00:56:02,441
I think I'm going to ask the director
to give Boi the part.

985
00:56:04,277 --> 00:56:06,653
- Are you serious?
- Almost positive!

986
00:56:06,738 --> 00:56:08,113
You won't be sorry.

987
00:56:08,656 --> 00:56:10,783
Trust me. I know.

988
00:56:42,065 --> 00:56:43,399
(RUMBLING)

989
00:56:46,861 --> 00:56:47,903
Oh!

990
00:56:47,987 --> 00:56:49,321
Oh, no.

991
00:57:04,629 --> 00:57:06,880
There are some changes for
the blocking in the dog scene,

992
00:57:06,965 --> 00:57:08,006
top of act two.

993
00:57:09,300 --> 00:57:11,093
Countess can learn these in no time.

994
00:57:11,177 --> 00:57:13,220
She's got a memory
like a digital hard drive.

995
00:57:13,304 --> 00:57:15,639
- No bark and all mega-bite.
- Funny.

996
00:57:15,723 --> 00:57:18,058
I need to find Sharpay
and make sure she gets them.

997
00:57:18,143 --> 00:57:19,768
Boi is doing
the first run-through tomorrow.

998
00:57:19,853 --> 00:57:21,603
I'd be more than happy
to deliver them to her.

999
00:57:21,688 --> 00:57:23,689
- Great.
- Thank you.

1000
00:57:25,150 --> 00:57:26,650
Thank you.

1001
00:57:31,990 --> 00:57:38,829
Sharpay?

1002
00:57:42,000 --> 00:57:43,167
(SIGHS)

1003
00:57:43,251 --> 00:57:45,002
That's unfortunate.

1004
00:57:45,753 --> 00:57:47,671
And I've been here ever since.

1005
00:57:48,339 --> 00:57:51,049
Life is so strange.

1006
00:57:51,134 --> 00:57:54,428
Shelby and I travel halfway across
the country to find fame and fortune,

1007
00:57:54,512 --> 00:57:57,222
and instead, we find love.

1008
00:57:58,057 --> 00:58:03,228
Lenore, I have something to ask you.
We have something to ask you.

1009
00:58:03,313 --> 00:58:05,063
(BARKING)

1010
00:58:05,148 --> 00:58:08,192
He's supposed to come from the other
side of the stage with the ring box!

1011
00:58:08,276 --> 00:58:10,903
Yeah, sorry. We changed that blocking.
What happened?

1012
00:58:10,987 --> 00:58:12,863
What is wrong with this dog?

1013
00:58:22,624 --> 00:58:26,001
And is he okay? It's not his fault.

1014
00:58:26,085 --> 00:58:30,130
He's just a little dog! He's just so sweet.

1015
00:58:30,215 --> 00:58:31,965
GILL: Okay, everybody.
Let's break for a few.

1016
00:58:32,050 --> 00:58:33,800
That's 10, people.

1017
00:58:33,927 --> 00:58:34,927
I'm aware. I know.

1018
00:58:36,513 --> 00:58:37,554
SHARPAY: I don't know
what happened.

1019
00:58:37,805 --> 00:58:40,182
We sent out the script changes,
but Boi didn't do them.

1020
00:58:41,017 --> 00:58:43,894
But I didn't get any new script change.

1021
00:58:44,646 --> 00:58:45,687
(SIGHS)

1022
00:58:54,697 --> 00:58:56,573
I looked everywhere last night
to give them to you.

1023
00:58:57,075 --> 00:58:59,493
I guess working for Amber Lee
has its drawbacks.

1024
00:58:59,577 --> 00:59:02,746
- You did this on purpose.
- That's a complete...

1025
00:59:02,830 --> 00:59:03,914
Yeah.

1026
00:59:03,998 --> 00:59:06,750
You're threatened because you know
Amber Lee is gonna choose Boi.

1027
00:59:06,834 --> 00:59:08,335
Not after today she won't.

1028
00:59:09,045 --> 00:59:12,422
Okay. Countess doesn't have
half the personality that Boi has.

1029
00:59:12,507 --> 00:59:14,925
And Boi doesn't have half the talent
that Countess has.

1030
00:59:15,426 --> 00:59:17,302
Isn't that right, girl?

1031
00:59:18,680 --> 00:59:27,813
- Countess?
- Boi?

1032
00:59:27,897 --> 00:59:30,440
- Has anyone seen Boi?
- No, sorry.

1033
00:59:30,608 --> 00:59:35,821
- Countess?
- Boi?

1034
00:59:35,905 --> 00:59:37,906
- Anyone seen Countess?
- Nope.

1035
00:59:38,700 --> 00:59:47,874
- Countess?
- Boi?

1036
00:59:54,257 --> 00:59:56,008
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1037
00:59:57,802 --> 01:00:00,178
- Hello?
- Boi and Countess are gone!

1038
01:00:00,263 --> 01:00:01,263
Gone! What?

1039
01:00:01,347 --> 01:00:02,389
We have to find them!

1040
01:00:02,640 --> 01:00:03,640
Wait, where are you now?

1041
01:00:03,725 --> 01:00:05,726
Leaving the theater.
We're gonna look around here.

1042
01:00:05,810 --> 01:00:07,394
Can you look near the apartment
in case they come back?

1043
01:00:07,478 --> 01:00:08,520
Yeah, yeah. Of course.

1044
01:00:08,605 --> 01:00:10,147
Just keep me posted,
and I'll call you if they show up.

1045
01:00:10,231 --> 01:00:13,108
Okay. What if they were dog-napped?

1046
01:00:13,192 --> 01:00:14,943
Do you think
we pushed them too hard?

1047
01:00:15,028 --> 01:00:17,654
- I don't know.
- Countess is über-sensitive.

1048
01:00:17,739 --> 01:00:19,740
She cries
watching dog food commercials!

1049
01:00:20,575 --> 01:00:23,035
I just hope they're not huddled
in a corner somewhere.

1050
01:00:23,119 --> 01:00:25,495
Afraid, lost, at each other's throats!

1051
01:00:25,872 --> 01:00:29,249
(SINGING) You knowyou love me
I know you care

1052
01:00:29,334 --> 01:00:32,919
Just shout whenever
And I'll be there

1053
01:00:33,004 --> 01:00:36,506
You are my love
You are my heart

1054
01:00:36,591 --> 01:00:40,302
And we will never, ever, ever be apart

1055
01:00:40,386 --> 01:00:44,514
Are we an item?
Girl, quit playin'

1056
01:00:44,599 --> 01:00:47,684
"We're just friends,"
What are you sayin'?

1057
01:00:47,769 --> 01:00:51,355
Said, "There's another"
And looked right in my eyes

1058
01:00:51,439 --> 01:00:54,483
My first love broke my heart
for the first time

1059
01:00:54,567 --> 01:00:59,446
And I was like
I thought you'd always be mine, mine

1060
01:00:59,530 --> 01:01:02,616
Baby, baby, baby, oh

1061
01:01:02,700 --> 01:01:06,286
Like baby, baby, baby, no

1062
01:01:06,371 --> 01:01:10,457
Like baby, baby, baby, oh

1063
01:01:10,541 --> 01:01:13,794
I thought you'd always be mine

1064
01:01:13,878 --> 01:01:15,420
I'm goin' down, down, down

1065
01:01:15,505 --> 01:01:19,341
And I just can't believe
my first love won't be around

1066
01:01:19,425 --> 01:01:22,969
And I'm like baby, baby, baby, oh

1067
01:01:23,054 --> 01:01:24,805
Like baby, baby...

1068
01:01:24,889 --> 01:01:27,015
SHARPAY: What if
we never see them again?

1069
01:01:27,558 --> 01:01:32,604
They're smart dogs.
Smarter than we are. They'll be okay.

1070
01:01:33,564 --> 01:01:35,232
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1071
01:01:36,901 --> 01:01:40,737
Oh, no. It's my dad. I just...
I can't deal with him right now.

1072
01:01:43,074 --> 01:01:44,157
(BOI BARKING)

1073
01:01:47,078 --> 01:01:48,370
- Countess!
- Boi!

1074
01:01:50,248 --> 01:01:51,415
Hi!

1075
01:01:53,209 --> 01:01:54,584
I missed you!

1076
01:01:55,503 --> 01:01:57,254
You're back!

1077
01:02:00,341 --> 01:02:02,426
It's amazing.
They came back to the apartment.

1078
01:02:02,510 --> 01:02:06,388
Thanks, Peyton.
Oh, and Sharpay, it's still on.

1079
01:02:06,472 --> 01:02:07,681
Bring it.

1080
01:02:11,769 --> 01:02:13,687
You're back! Yeah!

1081
01:02:14,605 --> 01:02:18,567
You bad, bad boy, Boi.
I'm just glad you're okay.

1082
01:02:18,651 --> 01:02:20,235
He and Countess had an adventure.

1083
01:02:20,319 --> 01:02:23,739
She probably coaxed him into
joining a doggy gang or something.

1084
01:02:23,823 --> 01:02:25,615
We'd better check him over for tattoos.

1085
01:02:26,159 --> 01:02:29,786
Are you so lost in what you're doing
that you haven't noticed?

1086
01:02:29,871 --> 01:02:30,954
Noticed what?

1087
01:02:31,372 --> 01:02:32,914
Boi and Countess are in love.

1088
01:02:34,333 --> 01:02:36,668
- With what?
- Each other.

1089
01:02:36,753 --> 01:02:38,003
No way!

1090
01:02:40,840 --> 01:02:44,968
You're right. He's dilated.

1091
01:02:45,470 --> 01:02:47,471
He's got puppy dog eyes.

1092
01:02:47,555 --> 01:02:49,639
How could I have not noticed
puppy love?

1093
01:02:50,141 --> 01:02:51,141
Well, there's a lot you haven't noticed.

1094
01:02:52,477 --> 01:02:55,145
Like lately, you've had no time for me.

1095
01:02:55,313 --> 01:02:57,647
You know, I was counting on you
to help me finish my film.

1096
01:02:57,732 --> 01:03:01,526
I said I would, and I will.
Things have become complicated.

1097
01:03:01,944 --> 01:03:03,320
It's not that complicated.

1098
01:03:03,404 --> 01:03:05,363
Amber Lee is using you,
and you're letting her.

1099
01:03:05,448 --> 01:03:06,782
You don't know
what you're talking about.

1100
01:03:06,866 --> 01:03:08,158
- I don't?
- No!

1101
01:03:08,493 --> 01:03:11,244
Where's the Sharpay that was
determined not to go back home

1102
01:03:11,329 --> 01:03:12,996
because she didn't want to work
for anyone?

1103
01:03:13,080 --> 01:03:14,664
Why don't you tell me?

1104
01:03:14,749 --> 01:03:16,249
Working for someone, that's where.

1105
01:03:16,334 --> 01:03:19,252
- So at least be honest as to why.
- I know what I'm doing.

1106
01:03:19,337 --> 01:03:21,505
You've sold your soul
to get Boi in that show,

1107
01:03:21,714 --> 01:03:23,632
rather than trust in the dog
that you raised.

1108
01:03:23,925 --> 01:03:25,759
Even worse, you've stopped trusting
that your own talents

1109
01:03:25,843 --> 01:03:27,677
would get you where you need to go.

1110
01:03:27,762 --> 01:03:30,931
And maybe you're jealous because I'm
on my way up with a new famous friend,

1111
01:03:31,015 --> 01:03:34,142
and you're just a student making a film
about someone else's life

1112
01:03:34,227 --> 01:03:35,685
instead of your own.

1113
01:03:40,483 --> 01:03:42,609
You don't have to be
in my movie anymore.

1114
01:03:42,693 --> 01:03:44,945
I get it.
You have more important things to do.

1115
01:03:45,029 --> 01:03:46,029
Fine!

1116
01:03:48,950 --> 01:03:49,950
One question?

1117
01:03:50,827 --> 01:03:54,246
What happened to that hot pink
whirlwind of confidence and ambition

1118
01:03:54,330 --> 01:03:56,456
I saw through my lens
that first day you got here?

1119
01:03:56,541 --> 01:03:59,000
I mean, that girl knew she was special.

1120
01:03:59,168 --> 01:04:02,295
That girl knew she didn't have to do
any of this to succeed.

1121
01:04:02,505 --> 01:04:04,714
What happened to her, huh?

1122
01:04:11,806 --> 01:04:12,889
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1123
01:04:14,058 --> 01:04:15,058
Hello.

1124
01:04:23,401 --> 01:04:27,779
Oh, and Sharpay, can you remember to
invite as many people from my fan club

1125
01:04:27,864 --> 01:04:30,156
as possible
to opening-night dress rehearsal?

1126
01:04:30,241 --> 01:04:34,327
I want the theater filled with people
who love me as much as you do!

1127
01:04:35,913 --> 01:04:37,080
Sure.

1128
01:04:38,040 --> 01:04:40,834
You know what would be great
after all this work?

1129
01:04:40,918 --> 01:04:43,086
A long, luxurious spa bath.

1130
01:04:43,170 --> 01:04:47,215
(SIGHING) Sounds amazing!
Thank you.

1131
01:04:47,300 --> 01:04:48,592
Run one for me, will you?

1132
01:04:48,676 --> 01:04:51,845
And then you can finish these.
You're the best!

1133
01:05:13,743 --> 01:05:15,201
(SIGHING)

1134
01:05:15,286 --> 01:05:17,871
- This is a big change.
- Huge change!

1135
01:05:17,955 --> 01:05:20,373
I don't think you're hearing me!

1136
01:05:20,458 --> 01:05:22,167
GILL: New Jersey can hear you!

1137
01:05:22,251 --> 01:05:25,045
The name of the show is
A Girl's Best Friend.

1138
01:05:25,129 --> 01:05:27,047
I didn't tell you to change the title.

1139
01:05:27,131 --> 01:05:29,132
But you want the best friend written out!

1140
01:05:29,300 --> 01:05:31,760
Oh. Right. Change the title!

1141
01:05:31,844 --> 01:05:34,846
GILL: How are we supposed to get rid of
one of our main characters

1142
01:05:34,931 --> 01:05:37,933
a day before our dress rehearsal
in front of an audience?

1143
01:05:38,017 --> 01:05:40,644
The audience is coming to see me.

1144
01:05:40,728 --> 01:05:44,064
You change that dog's part to a bark
and play dead, or I don't go on.

1145
01:05:44,148 --> 01:05:45,190
Let's be reasonable here.

1146
01:05:45,274 --> 01:05:48,151
I'm a star. I don't have to be reasonable!

1147
01:05:48,527 --> 01:05:50,362
Look, those mangy mutts
are bothering me

1148
01:05:50,446 --> 01:05:53,114
almost as much as
their disposable owners.

1149
01:05:53,199 --> 01:05:58,411
I actually had to have one of them
clean my toilet just to keep her away.

1150
01:05:59,330 --> 01:06:00,914
She thinks she's an actress.

1151
01:06:00,998 --> 01:06:02,415
(AMBER LEE LAUGHS)

1152
01:06:02,500 --> 01:06:03,917
She acts all right.

1153
01:06:04,001 --> 01:06:07,253
She acts just like
every other obsessed fan.

1154
01:06:25,439 --> 01:06:26,481
Wait.

1155
01:06:30,695 --> 01:06:34,531
Everything you said... You were...

1156
01:06:36,367 --> 01:06:37,575
Right?

1157
01:06:39,078 --> 01:06:40,203
Yes.

1158
01:06:41,872 --> 01:06:43,248
Thank you.

1159
01:06:44,417 --> 01:06:46,543
You must think I'm a total fool.

1160
01:06:47,294 --> 01:06:50,171
No. Not total.

1161
01:06:52,091 --> 01:06:53,591
Maybe my dad was right.

1162
01:06:54,552 --> 01:06:55,719
(CRYING) Maybe I'm not ready for this.

1163
01:06:58,973 --> 01:07:03,935
Maybe I should just go home
and... (STAMMERING) work for him.

1164
01:07:05,896 --> 01:07:08,189
I mean, did I really think
I was just gonna come to Broadway

1165
01:07:08,274 --> 01:07:09,274
and be a star?

1166
01:07:09,567 --> 01:07:10,608
Yes.

1167
01:07:11,694 --> 01:07:15,739
Because that's exactly how you think.
It's perfect.

1168
01:07:16,615 --> 01:07:18,366
Perfect is so hard.

1169
01:07:19,744 --> 01:07:21,995
And it doesn't prepare you
for disappointment.

1170
01:07:23,956 --> 01:07:28,585
Well, if it helps, you still look adorable,
even when you're disappointed.

1171
01:07:30,546 --> 01:07:32,547
Yeah, that doesn't help.

1172
01:07:35,301 --> 01:07:36,885
Look, Sharpay.

1173
01:07:37,928 --> 01:07:42,223
There is not a marquee big enough
or lights bright enough

1174
01:07:42,308 --> 01:07:45,060
to contain the fame you're gonna have.

1175
01:07:47,104 --> 01:07:49,856
Yeah, but not the way I've been doing it.

1176
01:07:49,940 --> 01:07:51,024
(SNIFFLING)

1177
01:07:51,108 --> 01:07:53,151
Like you said,

1178
01:07:53,235 --> 01:07:55,487
the Sharpay you know
isn't the Sharpay that has become

1179
01:07:55,571 --> 01:07:57,405
the Sharpay that is this Sharpay.

1180
01:07:58,282 --> 01:08:00,033
Did all the Sharpays follow that?

1181
01:08:04,038 --> 01:08:09,667
I sacrificed integrity for opportunity.
I let someone insecure distract me.

1182
01:08:09,752 --> 01:08:10,877
I cleaned a bathroom!

1183
01:08:12,671 --> 01:08:17,092
But worst of all,
I disappointed someone I care about.

1184
01:08:19,804 --> 01:08:21,805
I forgot what was really important to me.

1185
01:08:23,974 --> 01:08:26,392
I lost track of what I want.

1186
01:08:30,106 --> 01:08:34,859
And other than maid service and
a canopy bed, what is it that you want?

1187
01:08:38,030 --> 01:08:42,117
A fair fight. A lifetime in the spotlight.

1188
01:08:45,454 --> 01:08:47,705
And maybe you'll still let me be
in your movie.

1189
01:08:53,838 --> 01:08:55,130
I guess.

1190
01:09:07,226 --> 01:09:09,686
(CAR HORNS HONKING)

1191
01:09:24,160 --> 01:09:25,368
(SIGHS)

1192
01:09:28,497 --> 01:09:31,207
Okay, I can't say I approve of dating
beneath your station in life,

1193
01:09:31,292 --> 01:09:32,876
but fine. Go.

1194
01:09:53,898 --> 01:09:54,898
(EXCLAIMS)

1195
01:09:55,274 --> 01:10:00,278
Hey, I got your text.
What's C-Q-M-T-W-I-L-G-T mean?

1196
01:10:00,362 --> 01:10:03,072
"Come quick. Major trouble.
Wow, I look great today." Duh.

1197
01:10:04,742 --> 01:10:05,867
I really should have gotten that.

1198
01:10:05,951 --> 01:10:08,161
Listen, Amber Lee Adams
isn't what you think.

1199
01:10:08,245 --> 01:10:11,206
A self absorbed, two-faced panther
who would eat her young alive

1200
01:10:11,290 --> 01:10:14,542
on a reality show rather than allow
anyone to steal her spotlight?

1201
01:10:15,502 --> 01:10:16,794
Okay, she's what you think.

1202
01:10:16,879 --> 01:10:20,340
Listen, I don't care if her parents
had to tie beefjerky around her neck

1203
01:10:20,424 --> 01:10:22,342
just to get the family dog
to play with her,

1204
01:10:22,426 --> 01:10:24,385
as long as Countess is at her side
on that stage.

1205
01:10:24,470 --> 01:10:26,137
That's what I'm trying to tell you.

1206
01:10:26,222 --> 01:10:28,514
She wants the part of the dog
written out completely!

1207
01:10:28,599 --> 01:10:31,100
- That's not fair!
- Too far.

1208
01:10:32,102 --> 01:10:33,686
Well, I am 12, remember?

1209
01:10:33,771 --> 01:10:37,023
Roger, we've been fighting
the wrong battle, each other.

1210
01:10:37,107 --> 01:10:39,776
We need to form an alliance
and work against a common enemy.

1211
01:10:39,860 --> 01:10:42,445
- Zits?
- Amber Lee.

1212
01:10:42,529 --> 01:10:44,239
Trust me,
the zit battle is one you won't win.

1213
01:10:44,406 --> 01:10:45,573
But what can we do?

1214
01:10:46,367 --> 01:10:47,909
Tonight is the dress rehearsal.

1215
01:10:47,993 --> 01:10:49,661
The audience will be filled
with members

1216
01:10:49,745 --> 01:10:50,995
of Amber Lee Adams' fan club.

1217
01:10:51,080 --> 01:10:52,455
I know, I saw the tweet.

1218
01:10:55,125 --> 01:10:56,793
Fine. Yes, I follow her, too.

1219
01:10:58,254 --> 01:11:01,089
Okay, we need to show people
exactly who Amber Lee really is.

1220
01:11:01,173 --> 01:11:03,841
It's time someone taught her
how to behave in the theater.

1221
01:11:03,926 --> 01:11:07,512
I like the way you think.
It's manipulative, but for a good cause.

1222
01:11:08,722 --> 01:11:09,931
Tell me what you need me to do.

1223
01:11:15,604 --> 01:11:17,438
- Hey, Amber Lee, I...
- Where have you been?

1224
01:11:17,523 --> 01:11:19,232
I have been trying to reach you all day.

1225
01:11:19,316 --> 01:11:23,152
Oh. Sorry, my phone
must have been turned off.

1226
01:11:24,238 --> 01:11:25,822
Without asking me first?

1227
